So, if I prevent long-press gesture from being recognized until the pan gesture fails, the long-press would not eat up scroll anymore. 

First, I have `UITextView` subclass. In that subclass, loop through `UIGestureRecognizers` to `UITextView` at the appropriate point. I did it in method `didMoveToSuperview()`.
